%S A390200 1,2,10,72,710,8026,98353,1261889
%N A390200 a(n) is the number of n-celled polyplets (polyominoes connected at edges or corners) in the {4,5} tessellation of the hyperbolic plane.
%C A390200 This sequence was calculated in the context of a project in collaboration with Érika Roldán, and Rosemberg Toalá-Enríquez.
%C A390200 The term a(8) was computed by direct canonical expansion using exact algebraic matrices over Q(sqrt(2), sqrt(5)), with cells represented as cosets of the face stabilizer in the Coxeter group [4,5]. - _Pragyaan Gaur_, Jun 03 2026
%H A390200 Pragyaan Gaur, <a href="https://github.com/pragyaangaur/Hyperbolic-Polyplet-Enumerator">Hyperbolic Polyplet Enumerator</a> (contains Python implementations for exact enumeration).
%o A390200 (Python) # See GitHub link for exact algebraic matrix implementation.
%Y A390200 Cf. A119611, A030222.
%K A390200 nonn,more
%O A390200 1,2
%A A390200 _John Mason_, Nov 02 2025
